  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>The primary outcome of the Tranexamic Acid Study is the amount of blood loss per patient in the study.</measure>
    <time_frame>48 hours</time_frame>
    <description>We will be observing the amount of blood that is lost per patient in the accumulation of the chest tubes and bulb suction device outputs.
Also the total amount of blood given (in ml) to the patients in the form of blood and blood product transfusions (pRBC, platelets, fresh frozen plasma and cryoprecipitate)will be recorded.</description>
